# Optical Character Recognition for Historical Documents

An end-to-end OCR (Optical Character Recognition) system built using Python, OpenCV, Tesseract, and Tkinter, designed specifically for processing and translating historical documents. This project allows users to:

âœ… Upload scanned images or PDFs of historical texts
âœ… Preprocess images (denoising, contrast enhancement, sharpening, deskewing) for improved OCR accuracy
âœ… Extract text using Tesseract OCR (supports multiple languages)
âœ… Automatically detect language of the extracted text
âœ… Translate text into English (or other target languages)
âœ… Export results as PDF or Word (.docx) files
âœ… Use an interactive GUI with light/dark mode support

## Features

Advanced Preprocessing Pipeline

Noise detection and removal

Contrast enhancement

Image sharpening

Automatic deskewing

Adaptive thresholding for better binarization

Multi-language OCR

Supports English, French, Spanish, and German (can be extended easily)

Uses pytesseract with custom OCR configuration for accuracy

Automatic Language Detection & Translation

Detects the source language using langdetect

Translates non-English text to English using deep-translator

Export Options

Save results as PDF (auto-incrementing filenames)

Save results as Word document

User-Friendly GUI

Built with Tkinter

Upload images with a single click

View OCR output and translated output in pop-up windows

Toggle dark mode for better readability

